author: CNN
description:
Top Trump administration officials met with a Ukrainian delegation in Florida today. Secretary of State Marco Rubio said they made progress in efforts to end the Russia-Ukraine war but that “there’s more work to be done.” Rubio emphasized that Russia needs to weigh in on key sticking points when a US delegation visits Moscow this week.

CNN senior White House correspondent Kristen Holmes reports from Florida, and CNN's Omar Jimenez speaks with CNN contributor and former CNN Moscow bureau chief Jill Dougherty. #CNN #News
title: US and Ukrainian negotiators meet to advance revised peace plan

author: CNN
description:
When flames tore through the Wang Fuk Court estate in Tai Po, Hong Kong, William Li had no warning. A call from his wife was the first sign of danger. For more than two hours, Li and two neighbors were trapped, battling suffocating smoke and falling debris before firefighters pulled them to safety. CNN's Hanako Montgomery spoke with the escapee whose survival is a rare miracle in a disaster that claimed almost 150 lives and reduced his community of 40 years to ashes.

#cnn #news #hongkong #fire
title: How one man escaped from Hong Kong’s deadliest fire in decades

description:
Pope Leo XIV arrived in Lebanon’s capital, Beirut, on Sunday with the hope of being a “messenger of peace” as he begins a three-day visit to the nation battered by recent conflicts. Leo is expected to call for unity just days after an Israeli strike on southern Beirut. CNN's Christopher Lamb reports.

#CNN #News #Pope #Beirut
title: Large crowds welcome Pope Leo to Beirut

author: CNN
description:
With less than 48 hours to go, both parties have poured millions of dollars into the final stretch of Tuesday's special election in Tennessee's Seventh District, where Democratic candidate Aftyn Behn is trying to flip a district that Donald Trump won by 22 points in 2024.

CNN's Manu Raju speaks with Tennessee state Rep. Aftyn Behn on "Inside Politics." #CNN #News
title: Can a Democrat win a deep-red Trump district in Tennessee?

author: CNN
description:
The United States continued its pressure campaign against Venezuela on Saturday as President Donald Trump issued a broad directive on social media, warning airlines, pilots and criminal networks to avoid Venezuelan airspace. “Please consider the airspace above and surrounding Venezuela to be closed in its entirety,” he wrote in a Truth Social post. The announcement marks the latest turn of the wheel as the Trump administration intensifies its efforts to force Venezuelan President Nicolás Maduro out of office. Officially, the Trump administration says it is working to cut down on illegal flows of migrants and drugs — but regime change is a possible side effect of those efforts.

CNN's Manu Raju breaks it down with his "Inside Politics" panel: the Atlanta Journal-Constitution's Tia Mitchell, CNN senior reporter Stephen Collinson and USA Today's Susan Page. #CNN #News
title: Is Trump about to start a new war in Venezuela?
